name: Dumbbell Contralateral Forward Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending both knees until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your ankles. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and slowly lower your upper body towards the ground. | Step:4 As you lower, push your hips back and allow your knees to bend slightly. | Step:5 Lower the band towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your upper body back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squat On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side up. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and position yourself on top of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Lower your body down by bending your knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your weight on your heels. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and keep it off the ground throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Archer Pull Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 As you pull yourself up, bend one arm and bring your elbow towards your side, while keeping the other arm straight. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar and your bent arm is fully flexed. | Step:5 Lower yourself back down with control, straightening the bent arm and repeating the movement on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides with each repetition.

name: Lever Seated Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your knees are at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the footrests. | Step:3 Place your hands on the side handles for stability. | Step:4 Engage your abductors and slowly push your legs apart, away from the midline of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring your legs back together to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Rotary Calf
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your knees are slightly bent and your feet are flat on the footplate. | Step:2 Place your toes on the footplate, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Push through the balls of your feet, raising your heels as high as possible. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverted Row Bent Knees
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height and lie underneath it. | Step:2 Grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Position your body so that your heels are on the ground and your body is straight. | Step:4 Pull your chest up towards the bar by squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curls (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, while holding your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your arm extended in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow slightly bent and your shoulder blades pulled back. | Step:4 Slowly rotate your arm outward, away from your body, while keeping your elbow in the same position. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Handstand
instructions: Step:1 Find an open space with enough room to perform a handstand. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Kick your legs up towards the wall, using your core and shoulders to maintain balance. | Step:4 Once in a handstand position, engage your triceps to support your body weight. | Step:5 Hold the handstand for as long as you can maintain balance. | Step:6 To come down, slowly lower your legs back to the ground. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Full Planche Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, lean your body forward and lift your feet off the ground, balancing on your hands. | Step:4 Continue to lower your body until your chest is just above the ground. | Step:5 Push through your hands and extend your arms to lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Maintain a straight line from your head to your heels throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Find a suspension trainer and adjust it to an appropriate height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point and hold the handles with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Walk your feet forward, leaning your body forward until your weight is supported by the suspension trainer. | Step:4 Keep your body straight from head to heels, engage your core, and lower your chest towards the handles. | Step:5 Push through your chest and arms to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Deadlift With Stepbox Support
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Place your left foot on a stepbox or elevated surface behind you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, hinge forward at the hips, lowering the dumbbell towards the ground. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbell, simultaneously lift your left leg behind you, maintaining a straight line from head to heel. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell until you feel a stretch in your right hamstring, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Standing Lift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and position it at waist height. | Step:3 Engage your core and maintain a straight back throughout the exercise. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the cable handle up towards your opposite shoulder, rotating your torso. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Peacher Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. | Step:3 This will be your starting position. | Step:4 Now, keeping the upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

name: Band Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place a band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:2 Stand facing a step or platform with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:3 Step up onto the platform with your right foot, pushing through your heel. | Step:4 Extend your left leg behind you, keeping it straight. | Step:5 Lower your left foot back down to the ground. | Step:6 Repeat with your left foot stepping up onto the platform. | Step:7 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Lateral Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly lean your upper body to one side, feeling a stretch in your side and lats. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:5 Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, hinge forward at the hips and lower the dumbbell towards the ground. | Step:4 At the same time, extend your right leg straight behind you, maintaining a slight bend in your left knee. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell until your torso and right leg are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with your palm facing inward and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, straightening your arm. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Side Push Neck Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit up straight with your shoulders relaxed. | Step:2 Tilt your head to the right, bringing your right ear towards your right shoulder. | Step:3 Place your right hand on the left side of your head and gently apply pressure to increase the stretch. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, tilting your head to the left and applying pressure with your left hand. | Step:6 Repeat the stretch 2-3 times on each side.

name: Dumbbell Lying Pronation On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on the floor with your face down and your arms extended straight out in front of you, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Rotate your palms so they are facing down towards the floor. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, lift the dumbbells off the floor by contracting your forearms. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your forearms are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Front Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest lifted and your shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Engage your lats and pull the handles down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side-To-Side Chin
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body relaxed. | Step:4 Pull yourself up by bending your elbows and bringing your chin towards the bar, while keeping your body straight. | Step:5 Once your chin is above the bar, lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Middle Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach cables to both sides of a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand in the center of the machine with one foot slightly in front of the other. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and maintain a slight forward lean. | Step:5 Engage your chest muscles and bring your arms forward in a sweeping motion. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the center, then slowly return your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Stiff Leg Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, hinge forward at the hips, pushing your glutes back. | Step:4 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Assisted Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a pull-up bar or sturdy anchor point. | Step:2 Step onto the band and grip the bar with your palms facing away from you, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended, keeping your core engaged and your shoulders down and back. | Step:4 Pull your body up towards the bar by squeezing your shoulder blades together and driving your elbows down towards your hips. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rotation Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Rotate your arms so that your palms are facing downwards. | Step:5 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Grip Machine Lat Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest out and shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the handles down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand and step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Keep your upper arm close to your body and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:5 Extend your forearm backward, straightening your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell High Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Place the barbell on your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to squat down, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Twisted Flyes
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and press the dumbbells up to the starting position, directly above your chest, with your arms extended. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbells, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward at the bottom of the movement. | Step:5 Reverse the motion and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position, squeezing your chest muscles together at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Double Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand. | Step:2 Extend your right arm overhead, keeping your eyes on the kettlebell. | Step:3 Rotate your left foot 45 degrees to the left and your right foot 90 degrees to the right. | Step:4 Bend at the waist to the left, keeping your right arm extended overhead. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell towards the ground, reaching towards your left foot. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then engage your core and push through your right foot to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Kneeling Rear Delt Row (With Rope) (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low cable pulley and kneel down facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and extend your arms fully in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, pull the rope towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades. | Step:4 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement and hold for a brief pause. | Step:5 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Vertical Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footplate position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Alternating Arm Ups
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift one arm up towards your shoulder, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest, close to your body. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips down and back, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pelvic Tilt
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your abs and tilt your pelvis upward, pressing your lower back into the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, focusing on contracting your abs. | Step:5 Release the tilt and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Bent-Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing your body. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Let the dumbbell hang straight down towards the floor, with your arm fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Rope Crossover Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the rowing machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable ropes with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the cable ropes towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Elevated Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the elevated seat facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Grab the cable rope handles with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back, maintaining a slight bend in your knees. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully contracted position. | Step:6 Slowly release the tension and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Hammer Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell up towards your shoulder while keeping your palm facing your body. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement with the opposite arm. | Step:8 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Astride Jumps (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Jump explosively upwards, extending your legs and arms. | Step:4 While in the air, spread your legs apart and bring your arms out to the sides. | Step:5 Land softly with your feet shoulder-width apart, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push And Pull Bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 From the push-up position, pull your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:5 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Roller Seated Single Leg Shoulder Flexor Depresor Retractor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat surface with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Hold the roller with both hands, palms facing down, and place it on your thighs. | Step:3 Lean back slightly and engage your core muscles. | Step:4 Raise the roller up to shoulder level, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Slowly lower the roller back down to your thighs. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head, feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return the barbell to the starting position by reversing the motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Pike Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands on the floor and your shins resting on the stability ball. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, rolling the ball towards your hands. | Step:3 Keep your legs straight and your body in a pike position, forming an inverted V shape. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your upper body towards the floor, keeping your head in line with your hands. | Step:5 Push through your hands and extend your arms to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Close-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Using your thighs to help raise the dumbbells, lift the dumbbells one at a time so that you can hold them in front of you at shoulder width. | Step:3 Once at shoulder width, rotate your wrists forward so that the palms of your hands are facing away from you. This will be your starting position. | Step:4 As you breathe in, slowly lower the dumbbells to your side until they are about level with your chest. | Step:5 As you exhale, use your triceps to lift the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Twist Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbells, twist your wrists so that your palms face forward at the bottom of the movement. | Step:5 Reverse the motion and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position, squeezing your chest muscles at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez-Bar Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45В° Leg Wide Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the foot platform. | Step:3 Position your feet wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push against the foot platform to extend your legs and straighten your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bend your knees to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Standing Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band under your feet. | Step:2 Hold the band handles with your palms facing each other and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the band towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:2 Place a barbell on the ground in front of you, centered between your feet. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, to grip the barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:4 Engage your core and drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees simultaneously. | Step:5 As you lift, keep your chest up and back straight, and push your hips forward to fully engage your glutes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Drop Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Once your chest is just above the ground, explosively push yourself up, lifting your hands off the ground. | Step:4 As you push up, quickly move your hands out to the sides and slightly forward, allowing your body to drop down towards the ground. | Step:5 Catch yourself with your hands in the wider position and immediately lower your chest towards the ground again. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up motion, dropping down and catching yourself with your hands in the narrower position. | Step:7 Continue alternating between the wider and narrower hand positions for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Plank Hip Adduction
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Prop yourself up on your forearm, keeping your elbow directly below your shoulder. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 While maintaining the side plank position, lift your top leg towards the ceiling, keeping it straight. | Step:5 Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Assisted Lying Leg Raise With Throw Down
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Raise your legs until they are perpendicular to the ground. | Step:5 Lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Simultaneously, throw your legs down towards the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:7 Raise your legs back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Tricep Kickback With Stork Stance
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Bring your right elbow up to your side, keeping it bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Extend your right arm straight back, squeezing your triceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Curtsey Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step diagonally behind and across your body with your right foot, crossing it behind your left leg. | Step:3 Bend both knees as if you were curtsying, lowering your body towards the ground. | Step:4 Keep your torso upright and your weight on your front foot. | Step:5 Push through your front foot to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping diagonally behind and across your body with your left foot.

name: Cable Pulldown (Pro Lat Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your thighs are parallel to the ground and your feet are flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the lat bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and lean back slightly, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Muscle Up (On Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and pull your chest towards the bar, keeping your body straight. | Step:4 Once your chest reaches the bar, push down with your hands and drive your elbows back, lifting your body above the bar. | Step:5 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Muscle Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 As you reach the top of the movement, transition your grip so that your palms are facing towards you. | Step:4 Continue pulling yourself up until your chest is above the bar and your arms are fully flexed. | Step:5 Reverse the movement by slowly lowering yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twist (Up-Down)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips and legs stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the rotation to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (Wall) V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall, about arm's length away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back with your feet, keeping them hip-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:5 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the wall, keeping your body straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Standing Low Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a stable anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the band with one hand, palm facing inward, and step back to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pull the band towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the band back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Hip Lift
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place a resistance band just above your knees. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:4 Press your heels into the ground and lift your hips off the floor, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Shoulder Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest of the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles of the machine with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push the handles upward and forward until your arms are fully extended, but not locked. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbells at shoulder level, elbows bent and pointing out to the sides. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells up and slightly inward, keeping your palms facing each other. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Isometric Chest Squeeze
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground, with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles together as hard as you can, while keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, focusing on contracting your chest muscles. | Step:5 Release the squeeze and relax your chest muscles. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Hip Thrusts On Knees (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your feet flexed. | Step:2 Wrap the resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:3 Place your hands on your hips or extend them out in front of you for balance. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:5 Push your hips forward and squeeze your glutes as you lift your knees off the ground, extending your hips until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Hold the position for a moment, then slowly lower your knees back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down in front of you, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the high pulley of a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Engage your lats and pull the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Side Lying Adductor Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Bend your bottom leg slightly for stability. | Step:3 Place your top foot on a stable surface, such as a bench or step. | Step:4 Keeping your top leg straight, slowly lower it towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your inner thigh. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:6 Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

name: Band Close-Grip Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a high anchor point, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy beam. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point and grab the band with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back to create tension in the band, keeping your feet hip-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you pull the band down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the band back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press one dumbbell up overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back down to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place one foot behind you on a bench or step, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Hold onto the smith machine bar for stability. | Step:4 Bend your front knee and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Kneeling Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your feet hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then explosively jump up into the air, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As you jump, push through your toes and fully extend your ankles, knees, and hips. | Step:5 Land softly back on the ground, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Immediately go into the next repetition, repeating the jump squat motion.

name: Bodyweight Standing One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Let the dumbbell hang straight down in front of you, with your arm fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: One Arm Towel Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a towel with one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Extend your arm fully, allowing the towel to hang in front of you. | Step:4 Pull the towel towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the towel back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Ski Step
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Jump to the right, landing on your right foot while swinging your left leg behind your right leg. | Step:4 Immediately jump to the left, landing on your left foot while swinging your right leg behind your left leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating jumps from side to side, mimicking a skiing motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Overhead Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar down towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pulldown Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and slowly curl the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with one hand. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Slowly bend sideways at the waist, lowering the cable handle towards your knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulley is at the lowest position. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip and position your upper arm against the preacher bench pad. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Slowly curl your forearm towards your bicep, keeping your upper arm stationary against the pad. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your bicep. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Sled 45В° Leg Press (Back Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the sled machine so that your knees are at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grip the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push the footplate away from your body by extending your legs, keeping your heels on the footplate. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position. | Step:6 Slowly bend your knees and lower the footplate back towards your body, controlling the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Tricep Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the front of the bench with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:3 Keep your back close to the bench and your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse-Grip Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Using your triceps, push the bar down until your arms are fully extended and your triceps are contracted. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back supported and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell down towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Decline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine and grab the handle with one hand. | Step:3 Position yourself with your back against the decline bench and your arm extended straight in front of you. | Step:4 Bend your elbow and lower the handle towards your chest while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the handle back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever One Arm Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your head up. | Step:3 Let the barbell hang in front of you with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the barbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse-Grip Straight Back Seated High Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seat facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from your hips. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the cable back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Incline Chest Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest angle on the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push the handles forward and away from your body until your arms are fully extended, but without locking your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly bend your elbows and lower the handles back towards your chest. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Cross-Over Revers Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to each low pulley cable and stand in the middle of the cable crossover machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a pronated grip (palms facing down) and take a step forward, positioning your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and lean forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your abs engaged. | Step:4 With your arms extended out to the sides and slightly bent at the elbows, exhale and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the cables back and upward in a reverse fly motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the handles with your palms facing forward and your arms extended straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Chest Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in front of your chest with your hands shoulder-width apart, elbows pointing forward. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Lower Back Stretch (Pyramid)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the ball down your back until your lower back is resting on the ball. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lower your upper body towards the ground, allowing your lower back to stretch over the ball. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stalder Press
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended overhead. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position while keeping your arms extended overhead. | Step:4 As you squat down, press your arms down towards the ground, engaging your triceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to stand back up while simultaneously raising your arms back overhead. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Pulldown (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your thighs, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the rope back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Potty Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Lower your body down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back as if you were sitting on a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Reverse Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide reverse grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in and your wrists straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your upper back is resting on the exercise ball. | Step:3 Extend your arm with the dumbbell straight up above your chest, palm facing inwards. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Incline Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Grab a dumbbell in each hand and sit on the bench with your chest against the incline. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, allowing the dumbbells to hang straight down from your shoulders. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Elbow To Knee
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the ground, bringing your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:4 At the same time, extend your right leg straight out and lift it off the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, this time bringing your left elbow towards your right knee and extending your left leg. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold the cable attachment with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Pull the cable attachment straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Slowly lower the cable attachment back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intermediate Hip Flexor And Quad Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for support. | Step:3 Bend your right knee and bring your right foot towards your glutes, grabbing the rope with your right hand. | Step:4 Slowly pull your right foot towards your glutes, feeling a stretch in your right quad. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:6 Release the stretch and repeat on the left side.

name: Smith Chair Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Place the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you slowly lower your body by bending your knees and hips. | Step:5 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Arm Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a pull-up bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an underhand grip, with one hand gripping the bar and the other hand holding your wrist for support. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arm fully extended, keeping your body straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull yourself up towards the bar by bending your elbow and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Weighted Muscle Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 As you reach the top of the movement, transition your grip so that your palms are facing towards you. | Step:4 Continue pulling yourself up until your chest reaches the bar, then pause for a moment. | Step:5 Slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Calf Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leverage machine so that your shoulders are aligned with the lever pad. | Step:2 Place your toes on the lever pad, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or side supports for stability. | Step:4 Push the lever pad down by extending your ankles, contracting your calf muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly return to the starting position by allowing your heels to rise back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Place the arm blaster on your upper arms, ensuring a secure fit. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement with the opposite arm. | Step:8 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and push the bar down until your elbows are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand overhead. | Step:2 Rotate your left foot outwards about 45 degrees and keep your right foot pointing forward. | Step:3 Bend your torso to the left side, keeping your right arm extended overhead and your eyes on the kettlebell. | Step:4 Lower your torso as far as you can while keeping your right arm straight and your left arm extended to the side. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position by pushing through your right foot and engaging your obliques. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Assisted Standing Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired assistance level. | Step:2 Stand on the foot platform and grip the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and shoulders back, engage your core, and slightly bend your knees. | Step:4 Pull your body up by flexing your elbows and driving your elbows down towards your sides. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Low Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Butt-Ups
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, squeeze your abs and pause for a moment. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Wrap the resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:3 Place your hands on the sides of the chair or bench for support. | Step:4 Engage your abductors (outer thigh muscles) and slowly push your knees apart, against the resistance of the band. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring your knees back together. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that the handles are at shoulder level. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and lift them off the supports, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the handles down to shoulder level, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Press the handles up overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to shoulder level. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kipping Muscle Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and use a swinging motion to generate momentum. | Step:3 As you swing forward, pull your chest towards the bar, using your lats and biceps to initiate the movement. | Step:4 Continue the upward motion until your chest reaches the bar, then transition into a dip position by pushing down on the bar and extending your arms. | Step:5 Lower yourself back down to the starting position by bending your arms and controlling the descent. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Overhand Triceps Dip
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to the appropriate height and secure your body in position. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your body so that your arms are fully extended. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms close to your sides. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your elbows. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Full Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly shift your weight forward, lifting your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Continue shifting your weight forward until your body is parallel to the ground, balancing on your hands. | Step:4 Hold this position for as long as you can, maintaining a straight body line. | Step:5 Slowly lower your feet back to the ground and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Peroneals Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Loop the rope around the ball of your foot and hold the ends of the rope with your hands. | Step:3 Gently pull the rope towards you, flexing your foot and stretching your calf muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release the tension on the rope and repeat the stretch on the other leg. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Arm Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball With Leg Raised
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm fully extended. | Step:3 Place your other hand on your hip for stability. | Step:4 Slowly curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your bicep. | Step:6 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Roller Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Start by sitting on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Place the roller perpendicular to your body, just below your glutes. | Step:3 Slowly roll your body backwards, allowing the roller to move up your back. | Step:4 Continue rolling until the roller reaches your upper back. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly roll back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Incline Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the incline bench to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip, resting it on your shoulder. | Step:4 Push the dumbbell up and away from your body, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Incline Alternate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lean back on the bench and use your thighs to help raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Once at shoulder height, rotate your wrists so that the palms of your hands are facing forward. | Step:4 Push the dumbbells up with your chest and shoulders, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating arms.

name: Barbell Speed Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips back and down, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Close-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled One Leg Calf Press On Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leg press machine so that your knees are slightly bent when your feet are on the sled. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the sled, shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Place your toes and the balls of your feet on the sled, keeping your heels off. | Step:4 Push the sled forward by extending your ankles, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the sled back down by flexing your ankles. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf Stretch With Rope
