instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall or sturdy object with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the ends of the rope in each hand and place the middle of the rope around the ball of your right foot. | Step:3 Step back with your left foot, keeping your heel on the ground and your leg straight. | Step:4 Lean forward, keeping your back straight, and gently pull on the rope to stretch your calf. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release. | Step:6 Repeat on the other leg.

name: Tire Flip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the tire. | Step:2 Bend your knees and hinge at the hips, lowering into a squat position. | Step:3 Reach down and grab the bottom edge of the tire with both hands, fingers facing towards you. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and leg muscles, and explosively drive through your legs to lift the tire off the ground. | Step:5 As the tire flips over, use your upper body strength to guide it and maintain control. | Step:6 Once the tire is fully flipped, quickly step back and reset your stance. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Catch And Overhead Throw
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball in both hands at chest level. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Explosively extend your hips and legs, while simultaneously throwing the medicine ball overhead. | Step:5 Release the ball at the top of the movement and catch it on the way down. | Step:6 Lower your body back into the squat position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Bring your upper arms close to your sides, with your elbows bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Straight Back Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your upper legs. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent, hinge at the hips and lower the band towards the ground. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the band. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flexion Leg Sit Up (Bent Knee)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 At the same time, lift your legs off the ground, bending your knees and bringing them towards your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body and legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your bottom hand on the ground directly under your shoulder, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Press through your bottom hand to lift your body off the ground, keeping your legs straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Extend your top arm straight up towards the ceiling, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:5 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Isometric Wipers
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying flat on your back on a mat or bench. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, perpendicular to your body. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift both legs off the ground, keeping them together and straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower your legs to one side, aiming to touch the ground with your feet while maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then use your core to lift your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, this time lowering your legs to the opposite side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Breeding
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Start with your arms fully extended, perpendicular to the ground. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells slowly to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squat (On Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your shoulders, gripping it with an overhand grip and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you slowly lower your body down by bending your knees, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Seated Twist (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a weight plate or dumbbell with both hands close to your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverted Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height or use a suspension trainer. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar or suspension trainer, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grab the bar or handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back, keeping your body straight and your heels on the ground. | Step:5 Pull your chest towards the bar or handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie face up on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Cossack Squats (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a weight in front of your chest with both hands. | Step:3 Shift your weight to one side and lower your body by bending the knee of the side you shifted towards, while keeping the other leg straight. | Step:4 Go as low as you can while maintaining balance and keeping your chest up. | Step:5 Push through the heel of the bent leg to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, alternating between legs.

name: Cable Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Sumo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at hip height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper back and shoulders. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flag
instructions: Step:1 Start by gripping a vertical pole with both hands, palms facing each other, and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Using your core and upper body strength, raise your legs until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for as long as you can, maintaining a straight body line. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twist Hip Lift
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 While keeping your hips lifted, twist your lower body to the right side, bringing your knees towards the ground. | Step:5 Return to the starting position and repeat the twist to the left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, bending at the knees and hips. | Step:4 As you lower, push your knees out to the sides and keep your weight on your heels. | Step:5 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push To Run
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:3 Push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Quickly bring one knee towards your chest, then quickly switch and bring the other knee towards your chest. | Step:5 Continue alternating knees as fast as you can while maintaining good form. | Step:6 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with your arm extended straight up over your chest, palm facing inwards. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Engage your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Side Plank With Rear Fly
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, keeping your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in your top hand, with your arm extended straight down towards the ground. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:5 While maintaining the side plank position, lift the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable One Arm Decline Chest Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to a low pulley cable machine and set the bench to a decline angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your head towards the machine and grab the handle with your right hand. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:4 With a controlled motion, lower your arm out to the side until your hand is in line with your shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then reverse the motion and bring your arm back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left arm and repeat the exercise.

name: Cable Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Attach a straight bar to the cable. | Step:3 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight overhead. | Step:5 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:6 Bend your elbows and lower the bar behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Close Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Incline Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench facing away from the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with one hand and bring it up to shoulder height. | Step:4 Position your feet firmly on the ground and maintain a stable position. | Step:5 Press the handle forward and upward, extending your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Snatch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand between your legs. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips, lowering the kettlebell towards the ground. | Step:3 Explosively extend your hips and knees, using the momentum to swing the kettlebell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 As the kettlebell reaches shoulder height, rotate your hand and punch it straight up overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell back down between your legs and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand, feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell at shoulder height with your palm facing forward. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Bench Pull-Ups
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under a bar or a sturdy horizontal surface that is at chest height. | Step:2 Grab the bar or surface with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Pull your chest towards the bar or surface by squeezing your shoulder blades together and bending your elbows. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar or surface. | Step:6 Lower yourself back down to the starting position with control. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left foot and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your right leg extended behind you for balance. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body and your left leg slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Kettlebell Two Arm Clean
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of your thighs with both hands, palms facing towards you. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips, lowering the kettlebell towards the ground. | Step:3 Explosively extend your hips and knees, using the momentum to pull the kettlebell up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 As the kettlebell reaches shoulder height, rotate your wrists and catch the kettlebell in the rack position, with your elbows tucked in and the kettlebell resting on the back of your forearm. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows slightly flared out. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a pronated grip and keep your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Exhale and push the handles forward, bringing them together in front of your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, squeezing your chest muscles. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly return to the starting position, allowing your chest muscles to stretch. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rollerout From Bench
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the floor with a barbell placed on a bench in front of you. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly roll the barbell forward, extending your arms in front of you. | Step:4 Continue rolling the barbell forward until your body is fully extended and your arms are overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly roll the barbell back towards your body, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Grip Rear Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with a wide overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your head, neck, and upper back are supported by the ball. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up above your chest, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Bend your elbows slightly and lower your arms out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then reverse the movement and squeeze your chest muscles as you bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hands Reversed Clasped Circular Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Reach down with your hands and clasp them together behind your legs. | Step:4 Slowly raise your hands up and over your head in a circular motion, keeping your legs straight. | Step:5 Continue the circular motion until your hands touch your toes. | Step:6 Reverse the motion and bring your hands back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on an exercise ball and roll forward until your upper back is resting on the incline bench. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Lateral Bent-Over
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a cable machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with one hand and step back to create tension on the cable. | Step:3 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Extend your arm out to the side, parallel to the ground, with a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Smith Wide Grip Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the decline bench to the desired angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows pointed outwards. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Alternate Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the handles of the cable machine with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Position your hands at shoulder height, with your palms facing forward. | Step:3 Keep your core engaged and your back straight. | Step:4 Press one handle up and forward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:7 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Bridge V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:5 Lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side.

name: Lever T-Bar Reverse Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:4 Pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying flat on your back on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles, then lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking On Stepmill
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the stepmill machine to a comfortable level. | Step:2 Step onto the machine and place your hands on the handrails for support. | Step:3 Start walking by placing one foot on a step and then the other, alternating between legs. | Step:4 Maintain an upright posture and engage your core muscles. | Step:5 Continue walking for the desired duration or distance. | Step:6 Gradually increase the intensity or speed as you become more comfortable with the exercise. | Step:7 Remember to cool down and stretch after completing the exercise.

name: Kneeling Lat Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing back. | Step:2 Extend your arms overhead and interlace your fingers. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly lean to the right side, feeling a stretch in your left lat muscle. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the stretch on the left side, leaning to the left and feeling a stretch in your right lat muscle. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Posterior Tibialis Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Loop the rope around the ball of your foot and hold the ends of the rope with your hands. | Step:3 Gently pull the rope towards you, flexing your foot and stretching your calf muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release the tension on the rope and relax your foot. | Step:6 Repeat the stretch on the other leg.

name: Standing Archer
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, keeping your arms extended and your back straight. | Step:4 As you rotate, extend your right arm forward and your left arm back, mimicking the motion of drawing a bowstring. | Step:5 Hold the position for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the motion, this time rotating your torso to the left and extending your left arm forward and your right arm back. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Bridge Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Prop yourself up on your forearm, keeping your elbow directly below your shoulder. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 While keeping your core engaged, lift your top leg as high as possible without rotating your hips. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then lower your leg back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Split Squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and place it about two feet in front of the other foot. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, and your back knee is hovering just above the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Cable Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend at the hips and knees, lowering your torso until your back is parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders back. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift the cable handles, extending your hips and standing up straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Let your arms hang straight down towards the floor, with your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Stretch Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your knees until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Squatting Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to the lowest setting on a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the cable handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and knees behind your toes. | Step:5 As you squat down, curl the cable handle towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the curl, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inchworm
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist and place your hands on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Walk your hands forward until you are in a high plank position, with your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then walk your hands back towards your feet, keeping your legs as straight as possible. | Step:5 Once your hands reach your feet, stand back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, until your torso is almost parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest out and shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the handles down towards your chest, leading with your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge Two Legs On Bench (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start by sitting on the edge of a bench with your upper back resting against it and your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles, then press through your heels to lift your hips off the bench, creating a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Two Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your chest against the backrest and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip. | Step:4 Lean forward and let your arms hang straight down, fully extended. | Step:5 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Pirate Supper Legs
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise the kettlebell up to shoulder height, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Extend your arm fully overhead, straightening your elbow. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell back down to shoulder height, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Assisted Standing Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height settings. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your lats and biceps, and pull yourself up towards the handles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your back muscles. | Step:6 Slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45В° Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and footplate of the sled machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grip the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push the footplate away from your body by extending your legs, keeping your heels on the footplate. | Step:5 Continue pushing until your legs are almost fully extended, but without locking your knees. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the footplate back towards your body by bending your knees. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to chest level. | Step:2 Lie flat on the bench with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:3 Grip the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the bar and lower it towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the bar touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the bar back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope One Arm Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:4 Position your upper arm against the preacher bench pad, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Slowly curl the rope handle towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:7 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the rope handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Lying Close-Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie face up on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the bar towards your chest by contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Underhand Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulldown bar is at a height above your head. | Step:2 Sit down on the seat and grab the pulldown bar with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover Hip Extension On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and the dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the exercise ball down your back until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your arms straight and maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 While keeping your arms extended, lift your hips off the ground, squeezing your glutes and engaging your core. | Step:7 Lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bridge - Mountain Climber (Cross Body)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your right foot off the ground, bringing your right knee towards your left elbow. | Step:3 Return your right foot to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left foot towards your right elbow. | Step:4 Continue alternating sides, moving at a controlled pace. | Step:5 Keep your hips level and avoid lifting your hips too high or sagging them too low. | Step:6 Maintain a steady breathing pattern throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Prone Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, allowing the barbell to hang down towards the floor. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:7 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:8 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Skater Hops
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and jump to the right, landing on your right foot. | Step:3 As you land, swing your left leg behind your right leg and tap the ground with your left toes. | Step:4 Immediately jump to the left, landing on your left foot. | Step:5 As you land, swing your right leg behind your left leg and tap the ground with your right toes. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides, jumping and tapping the ground with each leg. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rocky Pull-Up Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a pull-up bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a weight in front of your chest or on your shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips down and back, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Push through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Hyper On Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with your hips at the edge and your legs hanging off the bench. | Step:2 Hold onto the bench for stability. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, raise them up towards the ceiling as high as you can. | Step:4 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Iron Cross Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:2 Raise your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Slowly lower your legs to one side, aiming to touch the floor with your feet. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return your legs to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the stretch on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Bar Lying Bent Arms Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold the EZ barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return the barbell to the starting position by reversing the arc motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone Twist On Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on a stability ball with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes touching the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Rotate your torso to one side, bringing your shoulder towards your hip. Keep your hips and legs stable throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Sumo High Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell with both hands in front of your body, arms extended downwards. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips into a squat position, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Drive through your heels and explosively extend your hips and knees, pulling the kettlebell up towards your chin. | Step:5 As you pull the kettlebell up, keep your elbows high and wide, and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jack Burpee
secondary_muscles: quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, shoulders, triceps, core
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, placing your hands on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Kick your feet back, landing in a push-up position. | Step:4 Perform a push-up, lowering your chest to the ground and then pushing back up. | Step:5 Jump your feet forward, landing in a squat position. | Step:6 Jump up explosively, reaching your arms overhead. | Step:7 Land softly and immediately lower back into the squat position to begin the next repetition.

name: Side Lying Floor Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight and your bottom arm extended straight overhead. | Step:2 Bend your top knee and place your foot on the ground in front of your bottom leg. | Step:3 Reach your top arm over your head and grab onto something stable, like a wall or a piece of furniture. | Step:4 Slowly lift your bottom leg off the ground, keeping it straight, until you feel a stretch in your side. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then slowly lower your leg back down. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side.

name: Bodyweight Standing Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a bar or handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the bar or handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: High Knee Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your right knee up towards your chest, while keeping your left foot on the ground. | Step:4 Quickly switch legs, bringing your left knee up towards your chest and lowering your right foot back down. | Step:5 Continue alternating legs in a running motion, bringing your knees up as high as possible. | Step:6 Maintain a fast pace and keep your upper body stable throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Smith Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the decline bench to the desired angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips while keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Prone Incline Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 45-degree incline. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Allow your arms to hang straight down towards the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Russian Twists (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Lean back slightly while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Twist your torso to the right, bringing the cable handle towards your right hip. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the cable handle towards your left hip. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a bench or step with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the bench or step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Push through your right heel and lift your body up onto the bench or step, straightening your right leg. | Step:4 Bring your left foot up onto the bench or step, standing fully upright. | Step:5 Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Lever Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and handles of the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and grasp the handles with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your arms slightly bent and your core engaged. | Step:4 Slowly pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your lats. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45° Leg Press (Side Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the sled machine so that your knees are at a 90-degree angle when your feet are on the footplate. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back flat against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grip the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push against the footplate to extend your legs, straightening them completely. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly bend your knees to lower the footplate back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (Wall)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall, about arm's length away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back a few feet, keeping your body straight and your feet hip-width apart. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the wall, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:5 Push back up to the starting position, straightening your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Clean And Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips, lowering the kettlebell between your legs. | Step:3 Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles, using the momentum to swing the kettlebell up to shoulder height. | Step:4 As the kettlebell reaches shoulder height, rotate your wrist and punch your hand straight up, locking out your arm overhead. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a stationary object at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with both hands in front of you. | Step:3 Keep your arms straight and lift them out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling your body down the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbells at shoulder level, elbows bent and pointing out to the sides. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells upward, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Split Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outwards. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your shoulders. | Step:3 Take a big step to the side with your right foot, keeping your left foot planted. | Step:4 Bend your right knee and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping out with your left foot. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dead Bug
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended towards the ceiling. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your legs off the ground, creating a 90-degree angle at your hips and knees. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower back to press your lower back into the ground. | Step:4 Slowly lower your right arm and left leg towards the ground, keeping them straight and hovering just above the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement with your left arm and right leg. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking On Incline Treadmill
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the incline level on the treadmill to your desired intensity. | Step:2 Stand on the treadmill with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Start walking at a comfortable pace, ensuring that you maintain proper form. | Step:4 Engage your core muscles and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Continue walking on the incline treadmill for the desired duration of your cardio workout. | Step:6 Gradually decrease the incline and speed of the treadmill to cool down before stopping.

name: Wrist Rollerer
instructions: Step:1 Attach a weight to one end of a rope or bar. | Step:2 Hold the other end of the rope or bar with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:3 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms fully extended in front of you. | Step:4 Slowly roll the weight up towards your hands by flexing your wrists. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the weight back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Sissy Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a weight in front of your chest with both hands, or place a barbell across your upper back. | Step:3 Keeping your chest up and your core engaged, slowly lower your body down by bending at the knees and hips. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Step-Up Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a step or platform with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your sides. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the step, ensuring your entire foot is on the surface. | Step:3 Push through your right heel and lift your body up onto the step, bringing your left foot up as well. | Step:4 Once both feet are on the step, lower your left foot back down to the starting position, keeping your right foot on the step. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, alternating which foot you step up with each time. | Step:6 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spine Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:4 Engage your abs and slowly twist your torso to the right, bringing your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the twist to the left side, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Delt Row (Stirrups)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a stirrup handle to a low cable pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and take a step back with your right foot, positioning your body at a slight angle. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 With your left arm extended and your palm facing down, pull the handle towards your chest by retracting your shoulder blade. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your shoulder blade. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:7 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with your right arm.

name: L-Sit On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the floor beside your hips, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Try to bring your legs parallel to the floor, forming an 'L' shape with your body. | Step:5 Hold this position for as long as you can. | Step:6 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Round Arm
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Continue lifting your arms until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Squat Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the band handles with your palms facing each other and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:4 Bend your knees and lower into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest lifted. | Step:5 From the squat position, pull the band handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and cable handles to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip at shoulder height. | Step:4 Push the handles forward and away from your body, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 30-45 degree incline. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back flat against the pad and feet firmly on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your upper chest, keeping your elbows slightly tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height settings. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended and your feet off the ground. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the handles, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the handles. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low position and attach the handles. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down towards the ground, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lift your arms out to the sides and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to waist level. | Step:2 Stand facing the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with one hand using an overhand grip, with your palm facing down. | Step:5 Keep your elbow close to your body and pull the bar towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Standing Cross-Over High Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to each side of a cable machine at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand in the middle of the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and maintain a straight back throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your shoulder muscles and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the handles towards the front of your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Gironda Sternum Chin
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a high bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Engage your lats and biceps to pull your chest up towards the bar, leading with your sternum. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverted Row V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height on a Smith machine or use a suspension trainer. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar or suspension trainer and grab it with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Walk your feet forward, leaning back until your body is at a slight angle. | Step:4 Keep your body straight and pull your chest up towards the bar or handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulley is at the highest position. | Step:2 Sit facing the machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the cable attachment with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:5 Pull the cable attachment down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the cable back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing inwards and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Place your other hand on your hip for stability. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell upwards, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.
